        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Children's Product Warning Label Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act to prohibit the sale of a cosmetic for children containing talc unless it includes a specific warning or the cosmetic is demonstrated to be asbestos-free. (Talc means a basic silicate of magnesium and includes talcum powder, hydrous magnesium silicate, non-fibrous talc, non-asbestiform talc, steatite talc, and fibrous non-tremolite talc.)</p>]]></text>
